description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Full Time - Bladder and Bowel Clinical Nurse Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;West Hertfordshire Adult Bladder and Bowel Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity to join our Adult Bladder and Bowel Service based at Hemel One supporting our amazing team of nurses who work in both clinic, virtually and home settings across West Hertfordshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal candidate will be extremely well organised, flexible, approachable and professional and above all compassionate to the needs of both patients and team members within the service and other health professionals. You will need to have a good sense of humour in order to blend well within the team, and a calm and considered approach to your work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essentially you will have a wide range of IT and computer skills or desirable that you have experience using System One or a Community NHS System, and feel confident in using bespoke systems with training and a range of other software packages. You will have an excellent range of communication and customer care skills, and will thrive on being part of a team, but also able to work effectively and autonomously with clinical support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the basic salary, this post attracts a High Cost Area Supplement of 5% of basic salary subject to a minimum payment of £1,017 and a maximum payment of £1,762 per annum (pro rata where applicable).&lt;/p&gt;
